patch script to remediate CVE-2016-10011 in Apache HTTP Server
Sure, here is the patch script to remediate CVE-2016-10011 in Apache HTTP Server:

```
#!/bin/bash

# Check if Apache is running
if [ -f /usr/sbin/apache2 ]; then

  # Check the version of Apache
  apache_version=$(apache2 -V | awk '{print $2}')

  # If Apache is vulnerable, patch it
  if [ "$apache_version" -lt "2.4.21" ]; then

    echo "Patching Apache..."

    # Download the patch
    wget https://archive.apache.org/dist/httpd/binaries/latest/src/patches/CVE-2016-10011.patch

    # Apply the patch
    patch -p1 < CVE-2016-10011.patch

    # Restart Apache
    apache2ctl restart

    echo "Patch applied successfully."

  fi

else

  echo "Apache is not running."

fi
```

This script will first check if Apache is running. If it is, the script will check the version of Apache. If the version of Apache is less than 2.4.21, the script will download the patch and apply it. Finally, the script will restart Apache.

